  "text": "Maximally supersymmetric Yang-Mills theory in four dimensions admits a topological twisting 1 which leads to localization equations of the form Here d A is the covariant exterior derivative associated to a connection A with field strength F = dA + A ∧ A on the gauge bundle E (a principal G-bundle over the four-manifold V on which the theory with gauge group G is defined.) The other bosonic fields are a one-form φ and a complex zero-form σ with values in the vector bundle ad(E) associated to E via the adjoint representation of G. There is a Lie product understood in the φ ∧ φ term, and * denotes the Hodge duality operator induced from the Riemannian structure on V . As described in [CITATION_1] , on an open four-manifold V of the form",
